17


The hugest dictionary in the library said under Lip: “Either of a pair of fleshy folds surrounding an orifice.”

Mileyshiy Emile, as Ada called Monsieur Littré, spoke thus: “Partie extérieure et charnue qui forme le contour de la bouche … Les deux bords d’une plaie simple” (we simply speak with our wounds; wounds procreate) “… C’est le membre qui lèche.” Dearest Em